louts continue to evolve, fans recently attempted to melt a giant ice block in the middle of Toronto as part of Drake&#39;s &#34;Iceman&#34; announcement. But how did we get here? NBC News&#39; Gadi Schwartz takes a look back at other memorable rollouts, and how they have advanced through the years.</description><expires>2056-04-30T17:46:04.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">now_staytuned_album_rollouts_260430</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/now/video/the-evolution-of-album-rollouts-262471749906</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/now_staytuned_album_rollouts_260430/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>The evolution of album rollouts</media:title><media:player url="https://www.nbcnews.com/now/video/the-evolution-of-album-rollouts-262471749906"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_04/now_staytuned_album_rollouts_260430-ytfzxi.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">As album rollouts continue to evolve, fans recently attempted to melt a giant ice block in the middle of Toronto as part of Drake&#39;s &#34;Iceman&#34; announcement. But how did we get here? NBC News&#39; Gadi Schwartz takes a look back at other memorable rollouts, and how they have advanced through the years.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/04/now_staytuned_album_rollouts_260430_1341.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/04/now_staytuned_album_rollouts_260430_1341.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_04/now_staytuned_album_rollouts_260430-ytfzxi.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 17:42:59 GMT</pubDate><title>The evolution of album rollouts</title><updateDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 17:47:40 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Phil Helsel</dc:creator><dc:creator>Mo Abbas</dc:creator><dc:creator>Daniele Hamamdjian</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Sun, 10 May 2026 05:01:11 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The cruise ship at the center of a deadly hantavirus outbreak arrived early Sunday off the Spanish island of Tenerife, where the process of sending most passengers back to their home countries will get underway.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/hantavirus-stricken-cruise-ship-arrives-tenerife-rcna344318</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/hantavirus-stricken-cruise-ship-arrives-tenerife-rcna344318</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-hondius-cc-0124a-9dc820.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1536" width="2048"><media:credit>NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Image: The MV Hondius, the ship at the center of a deadly hantavirus outbreak, arrives in Tenerife on Sunday. </media:text><media:description type="plain">The MV Hondius, the ship at the center of a deadly hantavirus outbreak, arrives in Tenerife on Sunday. After disembarking, passengers will undergo medical screenings before boarding flights that will take them back to their home countries, officials have said.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-hondius-cc-0124a-9dc820.jpg" height="1536" width="2048"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 05:01:11 GMT</pubDate><title>Hantavirus-stricken cruise ship arrives in Tenerife</title><updateDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 05:27:06 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Marlene Lenthang</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Sat, 09 May 2026 19:47:26 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>At least 15 people were hospitalized Saturday following a possible boat explosion near North Miami Beach</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/boat-explosion-miami-beach-rcna344365</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/boat-explosion-miami-beach-rcna344365</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-miami-fire-ch-1553-381ca5.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Jeff Greenberg</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Fire rescue vehicle.</media:text><media:description type="plain"></media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-miami-fire-ch-1553-381ca5.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 19:47:26 GMT</pubDate><title>15 hospitalized after possible boat explosion near Miami Beach</title><updateDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 19:47:26 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Nollaig O&#39;Connor</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Sat, 09 May 2026 19:00:53 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Even after more than 100 passengers and crewmembers fell sick during a norovirus outbreak aboard the Caribbean Princess cruise ship, passenger Jan van Milligen said life on board still felt surprisingly normal.“The normal atmosphere is still here,” van Milligen, who has spent the last 21 days aboard the ship with relatives and friends from South Africa, told NBC News on Saturday.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/caribbean/norovirus-outbreak-princess-cruise-caribbean-rcna344359</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/caribbean/norovirus-outbreak-princess-cruise-caribbean-rcna344359</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-Caribbean-Princess-ch-1448-8e67d8.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1666" width="2500"><media:credit>Ivan Pisarenko</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Caribbean Princess.</media:text><media:description type="plain">The outbreak sickened 102 of the ship’s 3,116 passengers and 13 crewmembers, according to the CDC.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-Caribbean-Princess-ch-1448-8e67d8.jpg" height="1666" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 19:00:53 GMT</pubDate><title>More than 100 sickened in norovirus outbreak aboard Caribbean Princess cruise</title><updateDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 19:00:53 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Matt Lavietes</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Sat, 09 May 2026 18:32:04 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Bobby Cox, the legendary Atlanta Braves manager and Hall of Famer, has died, the MLB team announced on Saturday.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/atlanta-braves-manager-hall-famer-bobby-cox-dies-84-rcna344361</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/atlanta-braves-manager-hall-famer-bobby-cox-dies-84-rcna344361</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-Bobby-Cox-ch-1430-f19e8f.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Stephen Dunn</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Bobby Cox.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Bobby Cox in 2001.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-Bobby-Cox-ch-1430-f19e8f.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 18:32:04 GMT</pubDate><title>Atlanta Braves manager and Hall of Famer Bobby Cox dies at 84</title><updateDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 19:21:23 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Francie Ebert</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Sat, 09 May 2026 14:57:40 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Betty Broderick, the woman convicted of murdering her ex-husband and his wife in their bed on Nov.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/betty-broderick-convicted-murdering-ex-husband-new-wife-dies-78-rcna344338</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/betty-broderick-convicted-murdering-ex-husband-new-wife-dies-78-rcna344338</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-Betty-Broderick-ch-1000-47d7cc.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Jerry Mcclard</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Betty Broderick.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Betty Broderick in San Diego in 1989.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260509-Betty-Broderick-ch-1000-47d7cc.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 14:57:40 GMT</pubDate><title>Betty Broderick, convicted of murdering her ex-husband and his new wife in bed, dies at 78</title><updateDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 14:57:40 GMT</updateDate></item></channel></rss>